Sentencas: K2NiF4-type structure oxide Pr2CuO4 is synthesized and evaluated as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Characterization and electrochemical performances of Pr2CuO4 as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrode forms good contact with the electrolyte after sintering at 950 degrees C for 4 h in air.
Titulo: Characterization and electrochemical performances of Pr2CuO4 as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The lowest polarization resistance (R-p) (0.56 Omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C in air) and cathodic overpotential values are achieved when the material is sintered at 950 degrees C on CGO electrolyte.
Titulo: Characterization and electrochemical performances of Pr2CuO4 as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Two main oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) processes are identified.
Titulo: Characterization and electrochemical performances of Pr2CuO4 as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The rate limiting step for ORR is the charge transfer process.
Titulo: Characterization and electrochemical performances of Pr2CuO4 as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The excellent electrochemical performance indicates that Pr2CuO4 can be a promising cathode material for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Characterization and electrochemical performances of Pr2CuO4 as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
